from\": 1678, \"to\": 1693}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Following this, they must raise the bar above their head, stepping one foot forward and one back, before bringing them both back inside, shoulder width apart, and tightening their body so they can stand still while holding the bar above their head.\", \"from\": 1695, \"to\": 1943, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the bar\", \"from\": 1727, \"to\": 1734}, {\"ngram\": \"their head\", \"from\": 1741, \"to\": 1751}, {\"ngram\": \"one foot\", \"from\": 1762, \"to\": 1770}, {\"ngram\": \"their body\", \"from\": 1869, \"to\": 1879}, {\"ngram\": \"the bar\", \"from\": 1918, \"to\": 1925}, {\"ngram\": \"their head\", \"from\": 1932, \"to\": 1942}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The snatch may not be as iconic as the clean and jerk but it is one of the most crucial moves.\", \"from\": 1947, \"to\": 2041, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The snatch\", \"from\": 1947, \"to\": 1957}, {\"ngram\": \"jerk\", \"from\": 1996, \"to\": 2000}, {\"ngram\": \"the most crucial moves\", \"from\": 2018, \"to\": 2040}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It involves competitors raising the bar from the ground to over their head in one single motion.\", \"from\": 2042, \"to\": 2138, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"competitors\", \"from\": 2054, \"to\": 2065}, {\"ngram\": \"the bar\", \"from\": 2074, \"to\": 2081}, {\"ngram\": \"the ground\", \"from\": 2087, \"to\": 2097}, {\"ngram\": \"their head\", \"from\": 2106, \"to\": 2116}, {\"ngram\": \"one single motion\", \"from\": 2120, \"to\": 2137}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In the inaugural games in 1896, competitors were required to perform a one-handed snatch.\", \"from\": 2140, \"to\": 2229, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the inaugural games\", \"from\": 2143, \"to\": 2162}, {\"ngram\": \"competitors\", \"from\": 2172, \"to\": 2183}, {\"ngram\": \"a one-handed snatch\", \"from\": 2209, \"to\": 2228}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, this was altered to a two-handed version at the Paris 1924 games.\", \"from\": 2230, \"to\": 2304, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2287, \"end\": 2297, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999998508429, \"rank\": 1.4934064353757226e-10, \"text\": \"Paris 1924\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a two-handed version\", \"from\": 2259, \"to\": 2279}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Athletes are permitted up to three attempts at each lift.\", \"from\": 2306, \"to\": 2363, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Athletes\", \"from\": 2306, \"to\": 2314}, {\"ngram\": \"to three attempts\", \"from\": 2332, \"to\": 2349}, {\"ngram\": \"each lift\", \"from\": 2353, \"to\": 2362}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Their best results in each lift are combined to determine their final score.\", \"from\": 2364, \"to\": 2440, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Their best results\", \"from\": 2364, \"to\": 2382}, {\"ngram\": \"each lift\", \"from\": 2386, \"to\": 2395}, {\"ngram\": \"their final score\", \"from\": 2422, \"to\": 2439}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Once a lift is successful, athletes can progress to a heavier weight.\", \"from\": 2441, \"to\": 2510, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a lift\", \"from\": 2446, \"to\": 2452}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 2468, \"to\": 2476}, {\"ngram\": \"a heavier weight\", \"from\": 2493, \"to\": 2509}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Each lift is judged by three referees.\", \"from\": 2512, \"to\": 2550, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Each lift\", \"from\": 2512, \"to\": 2521}, {\"ngram\": \"three referees\", \"from\": 2535, \"to\": 2549}]}, {\"sentence\": \"If a lift is deemed successful, they will turn on a white light.\", \"from\": 2551, \"to\": 2615, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a lift\", \"from\": 2554, \"to\": 2560}, 